task.summary:
Created a structure for tiles and a way for board to initialize itself with all empty tiles and to update all it's tiles.
Perhaps a private method taking a function and then goes through all the boards tiles and using the function on each tile would decrease code repetition.
Fixed javadocs and moved main method to Game class according to feedback from tetris
Fixed javadocs and moved main method to Game class according to feedback from tetris
Made a code analyze and fixed some of the problems

Merged the player class with the robots so it will be easier to connect moves depending on what robot you are using and since the player class only keept track of the interface it felt like it was a unnecesary class. Also added so you can turn left and right and so you can choose three moves before ending the turn and all three moves gets executed. You can not end your turn if you haven't choosen the three moves and you can't choose more then three moves. If you choose more the las one will be replaced. I've also added a remove move button so you can remove your moves.
Todo is to make it clear to the player which moves been choosen and if he can end his turn.

removed some unnecessary code in abstractRobot that was left from the way we intended to do the collisionhandling before.
Implemented push so that when a robot collide with andother robot it pushes the other one.
Started working on attack for the robots
Attack works but only one of the robots take damage
